cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.CG, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with the reconstruction of 3D models of human heads from Internet photos, which involves computer vision, graphics, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves 3D modeling and graphics, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Additionally, the paper uses photometric stereo constraints, which is a technique used in computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves computational geometry and optimization, which could place it in cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to grow the head mesh, which could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
